Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the annual meeting of the National Rifle Association (NRA) in Indianapolis. He expressed his support for the NRA and emphasized the importance of the Second Amendment and the right of law-abiding citizens to bear arms. Pence also praised President Donald Trump's actions in defense of freedom, including his support for the military, law enforcement, and conservative values. He warned of the threat posed by the radical Left and their push for socialism, and urged NRA members to continue fighting for freedom and to support Trump's reelection.